Congenital abnormalities in immature dogs from a pet store: 253 cases (1987-1988). In a pet store, 6- to 18-week-old dogs were examined for congenital abnormalities. Of those pups offered for sale over a 2-year period (1987 and 1988), 15% (253/1,679) had at least 1 congenital defect, and 1.5% (26/1,679) had multiple congenital abnormalities. Defects observed and their respective rates were patellar luxation, 7.2% (121/1,679) cardiac abnormalities characterized by murmurs, 0.7% (11/1,679)